@node what "What is this?"

				@{u}What is this little program?@{uu}

This small program lets you make a log file of any program you wish. It will also put
the program name in the log file so that you know which program has just been logged.

@endnode

@node use "Usage"

				@{u}Usage@{uu}

There are two parameters that need to be passed for this program to function:
	<logfile name> - which describes where the log file will be created
	<prog name> - which enables the log file to have the program name printed, therefore
                  allowing several programs to be logged on the same log file.
Note: This program is CLI-only (quite obviously ;^), so it must be run from a script to be
of any use.

@{i}Example:@{ui} (scripting example)

;start script

logtext sys:log.txt Myprog		;here the log text is appended to
run Myprog			;here the actual program is run

;end of script

Remember to make the script a "Project" type of file as opposed to a "Tool", as this will cause
the error "Couldn't open your tool `Myprog'". You can then assign a nice icon to it.

@endnode

